suncertify.util

Class Config

  • java.lang.Object
    • suncertify.util.Config

  • public final class Config
extends Object
    The class Config is responsible for reading and and storing the application's configuration properties. The first time the application is run it will generate the file "suncertify.properties" with default property values; these values can be edited by the user through the GUI. Each subsequent run will read the contents of the properties file so that the settings last specified by the user will be available without needing to re-enter them.
